history.content: Currently in both 186 and 161, it's been really manageable workload and content wise so far but I definitely believe that this is cause classes have also adjusted the workload to be more manageable for the current environment. Also, for 194-035, the instructors for the class currently recommend you either take 186 or 194-035 since there's currently a lot of overlap between the two courses. Overall, I really like both classes and they've been pretty great experiences overall

children.subject: Around the time where projects are due for both classes is pretty stressful ngl, but these are the only noticeable workload spikes. The projects require time and effort, but I'd say it is manageable if you start early (which honestly saves you a lot of stress) and have good partners. It doesn't mean that they are easy, but it is definitely feasible and not as overwhelming as other classes I've had
This is good to know. And yeah my partner and I are pretty diligent so I think we'll try our best to be on top of stuff. Thanks very much for your input!

@anon mouse thanks for the reply!

This will be my first time doing 2 full on coding + project classes in a semester, previously it would be like a coding + pset class or something like that. Does the workload drastically change around projects due around the same time for both classes or is it still fairly manageable?

Also thanks for the heads up on the instructor note about the overlaps. I saw this note from the professor but I for now opted for both because of the niche topics in 194 that I didn't see in 186. With that being said, I'll definitely keep the option of axing 194 in mind, just not for now as I definitely won't get back in if I change my mind.
